ODE XXV.

Glycera, a lady of great beauty, and a friend of Horace, being about to give an entertainment at her house, had in- vited him to attend it. We may suppose Horace, with his answer, to have sent this little neat and beautiful invocation to the goddess of beauty, requesting her to smile on the scene.
